abstract: Commonwealth Fund report finds there is little to no competition in private Medicare Advantage insurance markets in 97 percent of United States counties, with lack of competition even worse in rural markets.
lead_paragraph: An analysis of market share of insurance companies offering private Medicare plans found that nearly all American markets were already “highly concentrated.”

headline.main: With Mergers, Concerns Grow About Private Medicare
